The small and apolar residue Gly, which is highly
conserved between HA strains and is located at the
-terminus of HA2, has been shown to be a key
amino acid necessary for fusion. Deletion of this
Gly1 to either Val (G1V) or Glu (G1E)
pletely abolished membrane fusion and viral infec-
tivity, whereas a mutation from Gly4 to Glu (G4E)
resulted in less eﬃcient membrane fusion.
